text: Agdistis pseudocanariensis is a moth in the family Pterophoridae. It is known from Spain and the Canary Islands. The wingspan is 14–17 mm. The forewings are grey.Die palaearktischen Agdistis -Arten (Lepidoptera, Pterophoridae) ==References== Category:Agdistinae Category:Moths described in 1973
